This paper involves the application of Reinforcement Learning (RL) to solve the lane-change control problem in a dynamic driving environment. RL is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that deals with decision-making in an uncertain environment. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of a Deep Deterministic Policy Gradient (DDPG) algorithm, which is a type of RL algorithm that is commonly used in robotics and control systems. This makes cs.RO another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of a reward function and the optimization of hyperparameters, which are common topics in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG and cs.SY likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of simulation and video analysis, which are common topics in computer vision, making cs.CV a possible sub-category as well.
